description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting and challenging opportunity has arisen for someone who would like to develop in a busy, friendly team where your skills and ideas are valued and your development supported.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a 2 RMN Band 5 nurses, one full time 37.5hrs and one 30 hours on permanent contract to undertake the staff nurse role within Seren Unit within Older Persons Mental Health providing assessment and continual assessment of patients with a diagnosis of dementia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to be part of the team you will need to demonstrate an understanding of this service user group, and have a genuine interest and enthusiasm for caring for people with mental health issues, predominantly dementia. It would be advantageous to have an understanding and knowledge of the therapeutic approaches that work in such a setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 12th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jessica Hoyle - Ward Manager&lt;br /&gt;01443 443443 ex 74798&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jessica.Hoyle@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
